Remarks on N=4 Superconformal  


Extension of the Calogero Model  



Anton V. Galajinsky (galajin@mph.phtd.tpu.edu.ru, galajins@lnf.inf.it) 



Laboratory of Mathematical Physics, Tomsk Polytechnic University, 

634050 Tomsk, Lenin Ave. 30, Russian Federation 


and  

INFN-Laboratori Nazionali di Frascati, C.P. 13,
00044 Frascati, Italy 


 
Recently it was conjectured by Gibbons and Townsend that the large  limit of
an  superconformal extension of the -particle Calogero model might provide a
microscopic description of the extreme Reissner-Nordstrom black hole near the horizon.
In this paper a possibility to construct an  invariant extension
of the Calogero model is considered. We treat in detail the two-particle case and
comment on some peculiarities intrinsic to  generalizations.



PACS: 04.60.Ds; 11.30.Pb

Keywords: Calogero model, black holes,  superconformal invariance






The Calogero model  has many interesting physical applications.
It provides a nontrivial example of -particle integrable
system in one dimension (see Ref.  for a review). Calogero-type models are
related to semisimple Lie algebras  and reveal an intriguing connection with
Hamiltonian reductions of the  Yang-Mills theory . Higher dimensional
generalizations appear in the context of fractional statistics and higher spin gauge theories . In quantum area the one-dimensional system
turns out to be completely solvable (see e.g. Ref.  and references therein).

Quite recently the -particle Calogero model has been brought to focus again, this time
in the context of black hole physics . It has been known for a long time that the -particle Calogero model with the Hamiltonian
calogero 
H=1 2  _i=1 ^n  p_i^2  +1 2   _i<j   g^2 (x_i-x_j) ^2 ,
where  is a dimensionless coupling constant, exhibits the conformal invariance. The charges
charges 
D=tH-1 2   _i=1 ^n  x_i p_i, K=t^2 H -t _i=1 ^n  x_i p_i +1 2  _i=1 ^n x_i x_i,
are conserved and together with the Hamiltonian () form the  algebra
H,D =H, H,K =2D, D,K =K,
which is the conformal algebra in one dimension. The conjecture  that the -particle
Calogero model might be relevant for a microscopic description of the extreme Reissner-Nordstrom black hole,
at least near the horizon, originated from the fact that the near horizon geometry for this case
has the  isometry group, the bosonic subgroup being . Taking into account that
the extreme Reissner-Nordstrom black hole can be viewed as the configuration of
four intersecting supergravity -branes wrapped on   and assuming that each of the supergravity
-branes can be interpreted as a large number of coinciding microscopic -branes ,
one comes to the conclusion that there must be an  invariant mechanics which governs the
fluctuation of the branes in the region of the intersection . Being conformally invariant, the
-particle Calogero system provides a possible candidate(In the context of black hole
physics the large  limit is to follow .)  for the bosonic part of such an
 superconformal mechanics.

In this brief note we discuss a possibility to construct an  superconformal extension of the
Calogero model. We treat in detail the two-particle case and comment on some peculiarities intrinsic
to  generalizations. Throughout the paper we choose to work in the Hamiltonian formalism.

As the first step one has to decide on the number of fermions to be assigned to each particle.
Because the system must accommodate an  supersymmetry and since in the one-particle limit
one expects to reproduce the  superconformal mechanics  it seems
natural to append a pair of complex fermions , ,
obeying the bracket , to each bosonic canonical pair
 and .
Let us mark the fermionic degrees of
freedom corresponding to each particle by the superscripts  and ,
respectively(In order to make the formulae more readable we loosely put the index 
on both  and  down. A more proper notation would be
,  .) .
